/span><hr size=1> Beastlords just don't seem to fit in anywhere in the eye of the majority out there.  I have heard them called everything from gimped monks, wanna shamans, and melee mage wannabe and quite a few other things.   It's a great class to partner with things like chloroplast (mage here so I'm partial to anything hp regen) slows that aren't shammy but Bl slow &gt; than no slow, and now spirital purity.<br>
<br>
Also add in a strong pet and even nastier pet that looks to be maxed out at 51 with pop and more shammy like spells and I see the class being nastier than ever in the fighting category.  About the only thing I see wrong with the class from the view of playing with beastlords on a semi regular basis is maybe letting them have rouge armor restrictions and access to one hand slash weapons.<br>
<br>
But honestly outside hi h hi end stuff I think it's people not giving them a chance that has turned them onto a state of class depression like the old school magicians who tend to act as moody and dark as Marylin Manson why the new people like me are mostly happy with our class.  Sure you may want a shaman but why not give the beastlord a try instead of porting around the game world 3 hours to find one.<br>
<br>
Worse thing ya can do is try it and not be satisfied with the results but you need to at least try.  Heck grab a mage for mala and you get at least 80% of a shammy and meth sticks for mana.<br>
<br>
Mulkosaur Rex Lvl 57 Magician<br>
